# Frontend Development Rules

## Stack
React 18, TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind CSS, TanStack Query, TanStack Virtual, axios, Zustand, react-router-dom, lucide-react, react-resizable-panels.

## Dev Server
```bash
cd frontend && npm install && npm run dev
```
Runs on `http://localhost:5173`, proxies `/api` and `/auth` to backend at `localhost:8000`.

## Key Components
- `Uploader` — drag-and-drop pcap file upload (accepts `.pcap`, `.pcapng`, `.cap`, including tcpdump rotated suffixes).
- `PacketList` — virtualized packet list with protocol filter, substring search box, and pagination controls.
- `PacketTree` — expandable protocol layer tree; clicking a layer highlights its bytes in `HexViewer`.
- `HexViewer` — hex/ASCII dump of selected packet with highlighted layer byte ranges.
- `StatsTabs` — protocol hierarchy, endpoints (Tx/Rx), conversations, IO graph (bucket/metric controls); click an endpoint/conversation to filter the packet list.
- `FollowStream` — modal that reconstructs one TCP/UDP conversation's payload (ASCII or hex view), client vs server color-coded; truncation banner when the 1 MB/direction cap is hit.
- `AIAnalysisPanel` — per-conversation AI diagnostic summaries via SSE; also hosts the chat UI (thread list, message input, Stop button). LLM output is rendered as escaped text (no `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`).

## Pages
- `Login` — probes `/auth/me` on mount; GitHub OAuth redirect via `/auth/github/login`.
- `Dashboard` — upload area + captures list with status polling and delete confirmation.
- `Capture` — 3-pane inspector with view mode toggle (Packets / Statistics / AI Analysis), protocol dropdown, substring search, CSV/JSON export buttons, and Follow Stream launch from a conversation row.

## API Client
- `frontend/src/api/client.ts` exports an axios instance (`baseURL: "/"`, `withCredentials: true`) and typed helpers for all backend endpoints.
- The axios interceptor hard-redirects to `/login` on 401 unless already on `/login`.
- Chat streaming uses `fetch` + a `ReadableStream` reader (not `EventSource`, which can't POST) so the caller can pass an `AbortSignal` for the Stop button; SSE frames are split on `\n\n` and `[DONE]` terminates the stream.
- `packetsExportUrl(...)` builds a direct browser-download URL (cookie auth rides along on the GET) honoring active `proto`/`q` filters.
- Pages use TanStack Query for data fetching, caching, and invalidation.

## State Management
- `useAuthStore` (Zustand) holds the current `User | null` and `loading` state.
- `useCaptureStore` (Zustand) holds the selected packet index and protocol filter.
- `src/hooks/` exists as an empty directory; place future custom hooks there, not in `lib/`.

## Auth Flow
- GitHub OAuth: redirect to `/auth/github/login`, callback at `/auth/github/callback`.
- JWT stored in `pcap_session` cookie (httpOnly, secure in production, SameSite=Lax).
- `/auth/me` returns current user or 401.

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS with a dark theme defined in `tailwind.config.js`.
- Color tokens are `panel-bg`, `panel-header`, `panel-border`, `panel-text`, `panel-muted`, `panel-accent`, `panel-success`, `panel-warning`, `panel-error`.
- Default font is a monospace stack (`JetBrains Mono`, `Fira Code`).
- Wireshark-style row colors are defined in `src/index.css` (`.tr-tcp`, `.tr-udp`, `.tr-icmp`, `.tr-selected`).

## Build
```bash
cd frontend && npm run build
```
Output to `frontend/dist/`. Served by nginx in the test compose or by FastAPI `StaticFiles` in standalone mode.

## Testing
```bash
cd frontend && npx vitest run              # Single run
cd frontend && npx vitest                  # Watch mode
cd frontend && npm run typecheck           # App TypeScript check
cd frontend && npm run typecheck:test      # Test TypeScript check
```

Tests live in `frontend/src/__tests__/`, organized by `components/`, `pages/`, `api/`, and `lib/`. 13 test files cover:
- **Components** (7): Uploader, PacketList, PacketTree, HexViewer, StatsTabs, AIAnalysisPanel, FollowStream
- **Pages** (3): Login, Dashboard, Capture
- **App router** (1): routing based on auth state
- **Pure logic** (2): API client (axios), Zustand stores

`vitest` config in `vite.config.ts` uses `jsdom`, `globals: true`, and `setupFiles: ["./src/test-setup.ts"]`.
- `src/test-setup.ts` is a symlink to `src/__tests__/test-setup.ts`; edit the real file in `__tests__/`.
- Source imports use the `@/` alias resolving to `frontend/src/`.
- Test files are excluded from the app TypeScript build (`tsconfig.json` and `tsconfig.app.json` exclude `src/__tests__` and `src/test-setup.ts`).
- `tsconfig.test.json` extends `tsconfig.app.json`, includes tests + setup, and adds `vitest/globals` and `@testing-library/jest-dom` types.
